title: For Sale:  Phoenix Arms HP22A Deluxe Rangemaster Kit -LNIB-
postcontent:
After over a year of sitting in my gun closet, I think it's time to sell my HP22.
The gun is like new in the box, and includes everything that came with it originally.
I am the first and only owner, and never registered the gun, so you can register it with Phoenix and get the lifetime warranty.

The Deluxe Rangemaster kit includes:
- HP22A pistol with 3" vent rib barrel and 10-shot mag
- 5" extended vent rib target barrel
- Extra 10-shot mag with finger extension (more comfortable for folks with larger hands)
- Steel mag well gun lock
- Cleaning rod, bushes, patches (never used, I have my own cleaning kit)
- Tiny bottle of Break Free CLP cleaner/lube
- Manual, warranty card, misc paperwork, and iron-on "Phoenix Arms" patch
- All housed in a hard plastic, lockable kit that holds everything snugly for storage or transport.
Here's the Phoenix Amrs site with the full description of the kit and better photos: http://www.phoenix-arms.com/Products/HP22A_Deluxe.html

Please note that this is the DELUXE Rangemaster kit, not the regular Rangemaster. The difference is this deluxe includes both barrels and a second magazine.

Also included is a truly unique set of hand made not-quite-finished Black Walnut grips.
I made these in my shop, but never got around to final sanding and applying a finish. They're a little thicker than the stock plastic grips and feel a lot nicer in the hand for folks like me with larger hands.
They are functional as-is, but would probably take less than an hour to make them truly beautiful.

When I say this gun is like new, I mean you won't be able to tell it didn't just come out of the box unless you take it apart and see the little internal wear marks from firing.
I have put less than 1 50-round box of ammo through it in the year or so I've owned it.

This is a legally registered firearm, so you'll need to either come to my local gun dealer's shop to do the paperwork (permit required) or have it shipped to the FFL dealer of your choice, who will process the transfer for you.
I am willing to ship, but once you transfer it, it's yours. For this reason, I encourage local sales.

I am willing to do a full or partial trade for Ruger 10/22 parts/upgrades.
This is really why I'm getting rid of it. I'm moving to a rifle and don't need both.

title: For Trade:  Wicked Lasers Spyder Arctic III 1 Watt blue laser. Burns/Cuts/Melts
postcontent:
This is a brand new Wicked Lasers Spyder III Arctic 1 watt blue laser. Right off the bat, I'll tell you that you can go on to Wicked Laser's website right now and order this very laser for $299.99. However, I won't take anything close to that. The FDA (yes FDA) has put an import ban on any handheld laser above 5mw. This particular laser is 200x more powerful then what current import allows. Actually getting your hands on one of these is VERY diffcult. I'm a GM for UPS and even with my connections in customs, it still took me 6 1/2 months to get a hold of mine. From what I'm told 85% of these are seized.

However, once you DO have one, they are pretty incredible. It will burn or melt most things dark colored. You can cut through plastics, light cigs, pop ballons, start fires, etc. The beam is so powerful that if you pointed it straight up in the air, no only can you see the beam the entire way up, but the only reason it doesn't hit outter space is because our inner atmosphere diffuses the beam. If you were at sea, and pointed the beam straight out infront of you, the only reason you aren't able to see it past a certain point is because of the curvature of the Earth.



I understand this isn't what you typically see, so if you have any questions feel free to ask.

However, I won't take anything close to that. The FDA (yes FDA) has put an import ban on any handheld laser above 5mw. This particular laser is 200x more powerful then what current import allows. Actually getting your hands on one of these is VERY diffcult. I'm a GM for UPS and even with my connections in customs, it still took me 6 1/2 months to get a hold of mine. From what I'm told 85% of these are seized.

However, once you DO have one, they are pretty incredible. It will burn or melt most things dark colored. You can cut through plastics, light cigs, pop ballons, start fires, etc. The beam is so powerful that if you pointed it straight up in the air, no only can you see the beam the entire way up, but the only reason it doesn't hit outter space is because our inner atmosphere diffuses the beam. If you were at sea, and pointed the beam straight out infront of you, the only reason you aren't able to see it past a certain point is because of the curvature of the Earth.



I understand this isn't what you typically see, so if you have any questions feel free to ask.
